ed form, deriving its legitimate use from a democratic principle, the communal decision of the human jurors in the first case and the underworld gods in the second. Since discourse and reality were intertwined and the discourse was ritualized, actual violence might also have been partly ritualized. By still respecting the on-going desire to harm one's enemy, this partial ritualization of violence helped restrain violence and thus contributed to Athens' relative stability.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aTheaterzGreecexHistoryyTo 500. 0aViolence in the theater. 0aViolencezGreecezAthensxHistory. 4aGewalt. 4aKonflikt. 4aRache. 4aRitual. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Ancient & Classical.2bisacsh  aConflict.  aPerformance.  aRevenge.  aRitual.  aViolence.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Classics and Near East Studies 2000-2014 (EN)z978311062109908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Complete English Language 2000-2014 PART1z978311023857008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Classics and Near East Studies 2000 - 2014z9783110636178oZDB-23-GCN08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK GESAMTPAKET / COMPLETE PACKAGE 2012z9783110288995oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PACKAGE CLASSICAL STUDIES 2012z9783110293838oZDB-23-DGD08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PAKET ALTERTUM 2012z9783110288964oZDB-23-DGD0 cprintz978311024559240uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783110245608zOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110245608zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruy